Victor, squeeze my hand.

249
00:09:58,098 --> 00:09:59,642
Did you hit your head
when he attacked you?

250
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:00,776
You should quarantine...

251
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,361
Can you smile for me, buddy?

252
00:10:02,385 --> 00:10:03,913
Uh... JACKSON: No,
he's having a stroke.

253
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:05,848
There's pulsatile mass.
Could be damage to the carotid.

254
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:07,533
Maybe a pseudoaneurysm.
All right, get the ultrasound.

255
00:10:07,557 --> 00:10:08,797
I'm gonna book an OR.

256
00:10:09,576 --> 00:10:11,209
Mrs. Wiltern?

257
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:12,544
Uh, Walker. Marge Walker.

258
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,111
Take me home, Philip.

259
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:17,214
Mom? Uh, Sorry. She's
a little afraid of hospitals.

260
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:21,152
Oh, well, in that case, I'll
be very, very gentle, okay?

261
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,965
It says you hurt your leg?

262
00:10:22,989 --> 00:10:26,035
She says it was a bug bite
or something that got infected.

263
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:27,436
And then she said
it hurts like heck.

264
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:29,627
She's been popping
ibuprofen like it's candy.

265
00:10:29,696 --> 00:10:30,878
I had to drag her in here.

266
00:10:30,947 --> 00:10:33,631
It's fine. Philip, take me home.

267
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:36,195
Mom, no. Not until
you let her check it out.

268
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:37,596
Just try to relax, okay?

269
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:39,287
I'm gonna take a look.

270
00:10:43,126 --> 00:10:44,559
Uh, when did this happen?

271
00:10:44,645 --> 00:10:46,160
About four months ago.

272
00:10:46,229 --> 00:10:47,728
Four months ago?

273
00:10:53,453 --> 00:10:54,453
<i>Maggots.</i>

274
00:10:54,504 --> 00:10:56,671
Gross. Writhing and pulsing.

275
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:57,850
We know what maggots are.

276
00:10:57,874 --> 00:10:59,235
At first, they were
a little bit blurry

277
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:00,620
because my eyes... I
just had eye surgery.

278
00:11:00,644 --> 00:11:02,521
What? What? What
are you doing here?

279
00:11:02,545 --> 00:11:04,340
I'm fine. You shouldn't
be seeing patients.

280
00:11:04,364 --> 00:11:05,429
But I wanna be helpful.

281
00:11:05,499 --> 00:11:07,209
Well, great. Then
you can go to the store

282
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,761
any buy some Halloween candy.

283
00:11:08,785 --> 00:11:10,879
Name brands, none of
those Smarties or candy corns.

284
00:11:10,903 --> 00:11:12,403
But I'm not supposed to drive.

285
00:11:12,472 --> 00:11:13,899
Luckily, someone
invented the bus pass.

286
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,434
Come on, Grey. You're not
gonna make her take the bus.

287
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:16,608
Thank you, Dr. Torres.

288
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:19,956
There's a shop just up
the street. You can walk.

289
00:11:21,798 --> 00:11:23,375
You're looking for what again?

290
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:26,595
You know, one of those little
head mirrors that doctors wear.

291
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:28,085
Ben, you are a doctor.

292
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:29,949
Have you ever worn one? No.

293
00:11:29,973 --> 00:11:31,573
Because they stopped using them

294
00:11:31,608 --> 00:11:33,169
a century ago.

295
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:34,603
What are they teaching
you down there?

296
00:11:34,627 --> 00:11:36,605
Tuck wants to be a
mad scientist tonight.

297
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:38,190
He should have one of
those little head mirror things.

298
00:11:38,214 --> 00:11:39,680
Well, I have a brain in a jar.

299
00:11:39,749 --> 00:11:42,778
But I wanna give him a
costume, not a nightmare.

300
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:44,118
What did he do to you?

301
00:11:44,187 --> 00:11:45,848
Torres and I are working
on thought control prosthetics.

302
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:48,038
I'm trying to figure out a
way to insert the sensors

303
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:50,174
through a smaller craniotomy.

304
00:11:50,243 --> 00:11:52,677
Aw, you should be
ashamed of yourself.

305
00:11:52,746 --> 00:11:54,979
I'm sorry? Well,
that's for Zola tonight.

306
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,231
It was ripped. I fixed it.

307
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:58,144
Yeah, if you call this "fixed."

308
00:11:58,168 --> 00:11:59,628
I mean, I could do a
running whipstitch so smooth

309
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:01,964
the butterfly would never even
know there'd been a rupture.

310
00:12:01,988 --> 00:12:04,166
What are you teaching up here?

311
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:05,667
I would like to take a biopsy

312
00:12:05,691 --> 00:12:07,070
to see if the infection's
gotten into the bone.

313
00:12:07,094 --> 00:12:09,094
And we are gonna need
to take you down to the OR

314
00:12:09,162 --> 00:12:10,962
to clean the parasites
out of that wound.

315
00:12:11,031 --> 00:12:12,730
No! No! Take me home!

316
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:13,831
Mom.

317
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,394
Take me home! Mom. Mom. Mom.

318
00:12:15,418 --> 00:12:17,279
All right, we can give you a
sedative to ease the anxiety.

319
00:12:17,303 --> 00:12:20,315
No! No needles! No
needles! Just go away!

320
00:12:20,339 --> 00:12:23,979
Just leave me alone!
Don't! Just go away! Don't...

321
00:12:26,129 --> 00:12:27,378
She's always hated doctors,

322
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:30,030
but it's gotten out of
control since my dad died.

323
00:12:30,099 --> 00:12:31,477
I don't want to sound cruel,

324
00:12:31,501 --> 00:12:32,978
but can't you just
put her in restraints

325
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:35,086
and give her a
sedative or something?

326
00:12:35,155 --> 00:12:36,582
Well... I have an idea.

327
00:12:36,606 --> 00:12:39,846
I'm going to the gift
shop. I'll be back.

328
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:44,376
Put her in bed three.
Get an X-ray of the ankle.

329
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:47,843
Bed five should be empty.
Get a rapid influenza.

330
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,651
Could be the flu.
Right away, Doctor.

331
00:12:51,755 --> 00:12:53,988
Uh, ma'am?

332
00:12:55,659 --> 00:12:57,620
I'm waiting for my doctor.

333
00:12:57,644 --> 00:13:00,494
Well, I'm your doctor now, so...

334
00:13:01,932 --> 00:13:03,932
What's your doctor's
name? Maybe I can find them.

335
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:08,102
Dr. Brooks.

336
00:13:08,171 --> 00:13:10,338
Heather Brooks.

337
00:13:10,407 --> 00:13:12,106
I'm sorry. She's not here.

338
00:13:12,175 --> 00:13:13,708
Yes, she is.

339
00:13:14,544 --> 00:13:16,810
She's always here.

340
00:13:27,573 --> 00:13:29,919
<i>She said she'll only
see Heather Brooks.</i>

341
00:13:29,943 --> 00:13:31,587
Can I tell her about Heather?

342
00:13:31,611 --> 00:13:34,178
You wanna tell a sick old
lady her favorite doctor is dead?

343
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:35,747
That seem like a
good idea to you?

344
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:38,327
No. It's just, she's pretty
insistent on seeing Dr. Brooks.

345
00:13:38,351 --> 00:13:40,701
Then tell her it's not
possible and treat her yourself.

346
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:43,655
Um... Where is she?

347
00:13:43,723 --> 00:13:45,923
I don't know. She was
right there a second ago.

348
00:13:47,393 --> 00:13:51,395
Uh, Murphy's bitten, Edwards
is blind, and you're bonkers.

349
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:52,697
No!

350
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:53,915
Another one down.

351
00:13:56,903 --> 00:13:58,486
Holy...

352
00:13:58,555 --> 00:14:01,772
Ma'am, I'd like to get
you started on medication.

353
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:04,208
I need to know your name
so we can get you registered.

354
00:14:04,277 --> 00:14:06,828
No, I'll wait for Doctor...

355
00:14:06,896 --> 00:14:09,397
Dr. Brooks isn't here. I am.

356
00:14:09,465 --> 00:14:11,049
Just tell me your name.

357
00:14:11,117 --> 00:14:14,268
If you don't, I'll have to go
through all Dr. Brooks' charts.

358
00:14:14,337 --> 00:14:16,838
How about you save me all that
trouble and tell me your name?

359
00:14:16,906 --> 00:14:18,639
She'll come.

360
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:23,956
Okay, I'm tracking
one of the bullets

361
00:14:23,980 --> 00:14:26,280
through the accessory lobe.

362
00:14:26,349 --> 00:14:28,027
That's the middle lobe.

363
00:14:28,051 --> 00:14:30,418
Right. Right.
It's the right lung.

364
00:14:30,486 --> 00:14:31,786
Mmm-hmm.

365
00:14:31,855 --> 00:14:34,022
This is like driving in England.

366
00:14:34,090 --> 00:14:36,807
You know, I have to keep thinking
about every move that I make.

367
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,716
It's gonna take twice
as long as it should.

368
00:14:39,262 --> 00:14:41,696
Okay.

369
00:14:41,781 --> 00:14:43,448
You got plans tonight?

370
00:14:43,516 --> 00:14:47,785
Meredith semi-invited
me to this baby fest tonight.

371
00:14:47,854 --> 00:14:49,598
But I can't tell if she
really wants me to go

372
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:51,083
or if she just felt
she had to ask.

373
00:14:51,107 --> 00:14:52,968
It's so complicated. Right?

374
00:14:52,992 --> 00:14:54,953
She and I used to just know
what the other one was thinking.

375
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:56,093
I meant this.

376
00:14:58,998 --> 00:15:00,926
There's still bleeding
in the upper lobe.

377
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:02,361
I need more proximal control.

378
00:15:02,385 --> 00:15:04,018
Duval lung clamp.

379
00:15:04,087 --> 00:15:05,631
Straight vascular clamp, please.

380
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:08,722
Okay. Oh, watch
out for the SVC. Ah.

381
00:15:08,791 --> 00:15:10,725
Nicked the SVC. It
shouldn't even be there!

382
00:15:10,794 --> 00:15:13,827
I got you this so you don't
have to shut your eyes so tight.

383
00:15:13,896 --> 00:15:16,397
And you don't have to
see. You wanna try it?

384
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,772
There.

385
00:15:24,841 --> 00:15:26,301
So let's forget
we're in a hospital.

386
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:27,736
Let's talk about
Halloween. Okay.

387
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,072
Do you get a lot of
kids at your house? No.

388
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:31,195
Oh.

389
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,479
Too bad.

390
00:15:32,548 --> 00:15:34,493
All of the kids in the
neighborhood are Philip's age.

391
00:15:34,517 --> 00:15:36,917
They're all grown up and gone.

392
00:15:36,986 --> 00:15:40,638
But when he was little,

393
00:15:40,706 --> 00:15:42,089
it was nuts.

394
00:15:42,157 --> 00:15:43,541
A real madhouse, huh?

395
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:45,292
Yeah, kids everywhere.

396
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:48,245
Philip loved it. His
favorite holiday.

397
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:51,482
He always needed a costume
they didn't sell in the stores,

398
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:52,845
and I always
needed to make it...

399
00:15:52,869 --> 00:15:54,718
What's happening?

400
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,031
It's okay. We're just...
We're gonna take a little walk.

401
00:15:56,055 --> 00:15:57,866
We're gonna go down to
the OR and get you a gown.

402
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,034
Is that okay?

403
00:15:59,058 --> 00:16:00,675
Yeah. Yeah, but...

404
00:16:00,744 --> 00:16:03,611
It's okay. It's gonna be okay.

405
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:06,675
So you made all of his
costumes from scratch, huh?

406
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:08,883
What did he go as?

407
00:16:08,952 --> 00:16:11,452
Well, one year, he
went as an aardvark.

408
00:16:15,124 --> 00:16:17,202
Taryn's labs show a
slightly elevated white count,

409
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,660
and some of her
electrolytes are off.

410
00:16:19,729 --> 00:16:21,907
Um, is she gonna
be here overnight?

411
00:16:21,931 --> 00:16:23,142
It's just that her
dad wants to know

412
00:16:23,166 --> 00:16:24,760
if he should change his flight.

413
00:16:24,784 --> 00:16:26,962
Yeah, his eight-year-old has
a potentially surgical abdomen.

414
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:30,054
She needs a CT. She's in
pain. He should change his flight.

415
00:16:31,223 --> 00:16:33,401
Dude, what is your problem?

416
00:16:33,425 --> 00:16:35,303
I know you think he's
an ass, but he's not.

417
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:36,372
He's not your dad.

418
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,173
Don't even... What?

419
00:16:38,197 --> 00:16:40,192
Pretend that you're not angry
and hurt and about to explode?

420
00:16:40,216 --> 00:16:43,183
I've been doing
that. It's not working.

421
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:45,886
Tell me what I can
do to make this better.

422
00:16:45,955 --> 00:16:48,656
Just get a CT.

423
00:16:50,643 --> 00:16:53,421
So I thought the second
one would be easier,

424
00:16:53,445 --> 00:16:55,323
but it's just like having
one all over again,

425
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:56,814
except now there are two.

426
00:16:56,882 --> 00:16:59,161
So you're twice as exhausted.

427
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:00,713
Okay, we're all set.

428
00:17:00,737 --> 00:17:03,114
Okay. Okay, Marge,
we're in the OR.

429
00:17:03,138 --> 00:17:06,157
And we are ready to operate.

430
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:07,866
You'll be here the
whole time, Meredith?

431
00:17:07,893 --> 00:17:09,276
The whole time.

432
00:17:09,345 --> 00:17:11,145
Okay. Yes.

433
00:17:12,348 --> 00:17:13,564
I'm ready.

434
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:14,899
Okay.

435
00:17:14,968 --> 00:17:16,846
You know, if you
segmented the wings,

436
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:18,180
then she'd flap when she moved.

437
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:19,681
She just has to
look like a butterfly.

438
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,065
She doesn't
actually have to fly.

439
00:17:22,759 --> 00:17:23,959
How'd you swing the time off?

440
00:17:24,009 --> 00:17:26,877
You know, I just made it happen.

441
00:17:26,946 --> 00:17:28,824
Halloween was always
my favorite night as a kid,

442
00:17:28,848 --> 00:17:30,959
and I just wanted to spend
it with my family, you know?

443
00:17:30,983 --> 00:17:32,766
You're so domesticated.

444
00:17:32,835 --> 00:17:35,116
You're suturing a
butterfly costume.

445
00:17:35,455 --> 00:17:36,887
You know...

446
00:17:36,956 --> 00:17:38,534
You know, if we attach
this to her wrist with strings,

447
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:40,023
it'd sort of fan out.

448
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:43,026
That's a brilliant idea.

449
00:17:43,095 --> 00:17:44,945
Right. It's totally worth it.

450
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:47,198
Yeah, keep stitching.

451
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:53,916
They're incompetent.
It's not their fault,

452
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:56,290
because it's how
they were raised.

453
00:17:56,359 --> 00:18:00,093
These days, parents think
all of their kids are geniuses.

454
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:03,597
And everyone gets a trophy
just for being on the soccer team.

455
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:05,232
They're not the problem.

456
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,951
You are.

457
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:10,270
I'm trying to teach them,
and you won't let them learn.

458
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:12,940
I can barely get
out of this bed.

459
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:14,641
I can't operate.

460
00:18:14,711 --> 00:18:16,644
Who knows if I ever will?

461
00:18:16,713 --> 00:18:19,313
The only thing that
gives me some meaning.

462
00:18:19,382 --> 00:18:24,067
Hell, some days the only thing that
keeps me going is teaching them.

463
00:18:24,137 --> 00:18:27,472
And you're standing
in the way of that.

464
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:30,124
So I'm gonna have
someone else supervise them.

465
00:18:34,931 --> 00:18:36,925
You're not kicking
me off this case.

466
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:37,982
Yes, I am.

467
00:18:40,937 --> 00:18:42,636
This is why when I fire someone,

468
00:18:44,207 --> 00:18:45,689
I like to do it in their office.

469
00:18:47,944 --> 00:18:50,494
So I can walk out.

470
00:18:50,563 --> 00:18:53,180
Walk out, Bailey.

471
00:18:53,249 --> 00:18:55,065
Now.

472
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,363
Wow, there is barely

473
00:19:15,387 --> 00:19:16,553
any necrotic tissue here.

474
00:19:16,622 --> 00:19:18,722
The maggots might have
actually saved her leg.

475
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:20,368
Well, remind me to
send them flowers.

476
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:22,287
We may actually make
trick-or-treating tonight.

477
00:19:22,311 --> 00:19:25,496
Yeah, about that,
I'm bowing out tonight.

478
00:19:25,565 --> 00:19:27,726
Arizona and I can't be in the same
room for more than five minutes

479
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:30,912
before everything devolves
into gunfire and screaming.

480
00:19:30,936 --> 00:19:32,881
Sofia has been so
excited about Halloween.

481
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:35,417
I'm not about to let her
mommies' bickering ruin it, so...

482
00:19:35,441 --> 00:19:36,757
Taking one for the team.

483
00:19:36,826 --> 00:19:39,459
Are you sure? There's
gonna be a pinata.

484
00:19:39,528 --> 00:19:41,257
Shut up. And pin the
head on the skeleton.

485
00:19:41,281 --> 00:19:43,931
Damn it! They're so cute
when they're blindfolded.

486
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,966
Bobbing for apples. Aw!

487
00:19:46,035 --> 00:19:47,545
They're even cuter
when they bob!

488
00:19:47,569 --> 00:19:49,147
I'll take pictures.

489
00:19:49,171 --> 00:19:50,754
Dr. Grey, it's Dr. Webber.

490
00:19:50,823 --> 00:19:52,318
He's asking whether you
have room on your schedule

491
00:19:52,342 --> 00:19:53,582
for a cystogastrostomy.

492
00:19:55,011 --> 00:19:57,292
Maybe Derek can take pictures.

493
00:19:59,348 --> 00:20:00,893
Did you get your labs back?

494
00:20:00,917 --> 00:20:02,450
Nope.

495
00:20:02,518 --> 00:20:05,030
The post exposure counselor
gave me this cheerful little pamphlet

496
00:20:05,054 --> 00:20:09,073
on anti-viral drugs to
read while I'm waiting.

497
00:20:09,141 --> 00:20:10,819
She said in case I do have HIV,

498
00:20:10,843 --> 00:20:13,355
it might not be a bad idea
to start taking them now.

