00:31:25,934 --> 00:31:28,368
You what?

752
00:31:28,437 --> 00:31:31,166
Hey, have you seen Wilson?
'Cause I need to get an update on...

753
00:31:31,190 --> 00:31:33,239
What's wrong?

754
00:31:33,308 --> 00:31:34,386
Nothing's wrong. I'm fine.

755
00:31:34,410 --> 00:31:35,410
You're crying.

756
00:31:36,945 --> 00:31:38,394
It's nothing. I'm fine.

757
00:31:40,765 --> 00:31:45,285
I got bit by a delusional,
psychotic drug addict

758
00:31:45,354 --> 00:31:47,604
who think he's the undead.

759
00:31:47,673 --> 00:31:50,507
And I'm waiting for
the guy's HIV results.

760
00:31:50,576 --> 00:31:51,841
Why didn't you tell me?

761
00:31:53,278 --> 00:31:55,245
I'm trying to be easy peasy.

762
00:32:08,076 --> 00:32:10,560
My first needle stick
happened on a Tuesday.

763
00:32:12,464 --> 00:32:14,965
It was the second
month of my third year

764
00:32:15,033 --> 00:32:17,917
in my internal
medicine rotation.

765
00:32:17,986 --> 00:32:21,854
And my patient was
suffering from end stage AIDS.

766
00:32:23,791 --> 00:32:26,826
We had just switched over
to these retractable needles.

767
00:32:26,895 --> 00:32:31,431
And when I went to put his
into the hazardous waste,

768
00:32:33,168 --> 00:32:36,036
I didn't retract it right.

769
00:32:36,104 --> 00:32:39,839
And it jammed
right into my palm.

770
00:32:39,908 --> 00:32:42,042
And my whole body went cold.

771
00:32:44,312 --> 00:32:49,883
And I had never felt fear
like that in my whole life.

772
00:32:53,856 --> 00:32:56,390
Right now,

773
00:32:56,458 --> 00:32:59,158
it's not the time
to be easy peasy.

774
00:33:15,811 --> 00:33:16,926
She's dead.

775
00:33:20,832 --> 00:33:23,149
Dr. Brooks died
three months ago.

776
00:33:27,272 --> 00:33:29,456
Well, that can't be true.

777
00:33:34,112 --> 00:33:37,246
You're not in the charts.

778
00:33:37,315 --> 00:33:39,582
She was treating you
under the table, right?

779
00:33:44,923 --> 00:33:48,624
She was giving you
these for your asthma?

780
00:33:50,912 --> 00:33:53,679
I didn't want her
to get into trouble.

781
00:33:56,418 --> 00:33:57,901
When you run out,

782
00:33:57,969 --> 00:34:00,337
you come back, you find me.

783
00:34:01,973 --> 00:34:03,940
I'll be your doctor now.

784
00:34:05,661 --> 00:34:07,661
She was a very good doctor.

785
00:34:09,531 --> 00:34:11,981
Are you as good as she was?

786
00:34:15,637 --> 00:34:16,669
No.

787
00:34:19,173 --> 00:34:20,406
But I will be.

788
00:34:30,001 --> 00:34:32,535
So there's the wall
of the pseudocyst.

789
00:34:32,604 --> 00:34:34,070
Now what do you do?

790
00:34:34,139 --> 00:34:35,983
Enlarge the incision with
a dissecting instrument

791
00:34:36,007 --> 00:34:38,257
and use a stapler to
create the anastomosis.

792
00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:40,343
Good. Carry on.

793
00:34:40,412 --> 00:34:42,329
Faster, but take your time.

794
00:34:42,397 --> 00:34:44,392
Can I tell you a
thing about Alex?

795
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:47,062
He doesn't want me to tell
anyone, but I don't know what to do.

796
00:34:47,086 --> 00:34:49,119
He keeps pushing me away.

797
00:34:49,188 --> 00:34:50,615
And you know
him better than I do.

798
00:34:50,639 --> 00:34:51,738
Can't tell me.

799
00:34:51,806 --> 00:34:53,073
I can't?

800
00:34:53,141 --> 00:34:54,502
Telling me is the worst
thing you could do.

801
00:34:54,526 --> 00:34:55,992
If he told you, he trusted you.

802
00:34:56,060 --> 00:34:58,778
So whatever it is, you have
to be the one to deal with it.

803
00:34:58,847 --> 00:35:00,492
I mean, of course he's
gonna to push you away,

804
00:35:00,516 --> 00:35:02,114
because he hates
being vulnerable.

805
00:35:02,183 --> 00:35:04,743
But that's when he's gonna
need you to stick with him the most.

806
00:35:05,771 --> 00:35:06,953
I'll keep trying.

807
00:35:07,022 --> 00:35:08,399
We'll, you're gonna
have to do better than try,

808
00:35:08,423 --> 00:35:09,573
because my plate is full.

809
00:35:09,641 --> 00:35:11,875
I have too many kids
and too many patients,

810
00:35:11,944 --> 00:35:14,410
and I can't handle a
broken Alex right now.

811
00:35:14,479 --> 00:35:17,247
You can do it.

812
00:35:17,316 --> 00:35:21,451
Is it out of the question to get a
little consistency in this family?

813
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,502
What consistency?
I never see you.

814
00:35:26,308 --> 00:35:28,228
Trick-or-treat!
Oh, trick-or-treat.

815
00:35:28,293 --> 00:35:29,971
Look at you. You're so scary.

816
00:35:29,995 --> 00:35:31,439
Here.

817
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:33,363
Thank you.

818
00:35:34,682 --> 00:35:36,449
You started the program.

819
00:35:36,518 --> 00:35:39,002
No, you upended
our lives because

820
00:35:39,070 --> 00:35:41,454
it was extremely
important to you.

821
00:35:41,522 --> 00:35:42,883
It's not working.

822
00:35:42,907 --> 00:35:45,975
You are my family, and
I want to be with you.

823
00:35:46,044 --> 00:35:49,546
Trick-or-treat! Oh,
Cleopatra and a ladybug.

824
00:35:49,615 --> 00:35:50,814
Thank you.

825
00:35:50,883 --> 00:35:52,098
Trick-or-treat!

826
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:56,903
My life is happening,
and I'm elsewhere.

827
00:35:56,971 --> 00:35:58,287
You don't love it?

828
00:35:58,357 --> 00:36:00,022
You? Of course I...

829
00:36:00,091 --> 00:36:02,992
No, not me. Surgery.

830
00:36:03,061 --> 00:36:06,262
You left town a week
after we got married

831
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:08,531
to learn surgery, because...

832
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:11,534
You were in love with it.

833
00:36:11,603 --> 00:36:15,154
Yeah. But I am in
love with you more.

834
00:36:16,941 --> 00:36:18,941
You really gonna tell me
that's the wrong answer?

835
00:36:19,077 --> 00:36:20,210
I'm just...

836
00:36:22,147 --> 00:36:23,387
What?

837
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:25,882
Miranda, what?

838
00:36:25,951 --> 00:36:28,284
Disappointed.

839
00:36:28,353 --> 00:36:29,553
In you.

840
00:36:34,726 --> 00:36:36,006
Can we go trick-or-treating now?

841
00:36:37,212 --> 00:36:40,346
You are so cute!

842
00:36:40,415 --> 00:36:42,131
Oh...

843
00:36:42,201 --> 00:36:44,918
Okay. Let me get my coat.

844
00:36:54,095 --> 00:36:56,207
<i>This is Emma Marling.
Please leave a message.</i>

845
00:36:56,231 --> 00:36:58,497
Emma, Owen.

846
00:36:58,566 --> 00:37:01,034
Uh, Listen, um...

847
00:37:01,102 --> 00:37:03,414
I wasn't ready to talk
about Cristina before,

848
00:37:03,438 --> 00:37:07,440
because things between she
and I were always so complicated.

849
00:37:07,508 --> 00:37:10,210
And I can't... I can't do
complicated right now.

850
00:37:10,278 --> 00:37:12,556
I don't even want to
think about complicated,

851
00:37:12,580 --> 00:37:15,315
and that is what is
so great about you,

852
00:37:15,383 --> 00:37:18,351
is that you're, you
know, you're so easy.

853
00:37:18,419 --> 00:37:20,832
God, that came out wrong.
I don't mean you're easy.

854
00:37:20,856 --> 00:37:22,388
I mean you're simple.

855
00:37:25,260 --> 00:37:27,104
Delete this.

856
00:37:33,101 --> 00:37:34,778
Emma? <i>Hi.</i>

857
00:37:34,802 --> 00:37:36,069
Hey.

858
00:37:36,138 --> 00:37:38,371
How'd she do? Fantastic.

859
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,757
Almost as if she
had a great teacher.

860
00:37:40,826 --> 00:37:43,576
Take me through it. I
want to hear every detail.

861
00:37:43,645 --> 00:37:45,178
Well, in the interest
of education,

862
00:37:45,247 --> 00:37:47,247
why don't we let
Dr. Wilson do that?

863
00:37:47,315 --> 00:37:49,599
I like the way you think, Grey.

864
00:37:49,667 --> 00:37:52,302
Okay, well, we started
your incision using...

865
00:37:52,370 --> 00:37:54,820
No, no. Start from
the very beginning.

866
00:37:57,191 --> 00:37:58,775
Where'd you place the ports?

867
00:37:58,843 --> 00:38:01,711
Well, um, we took a look
at your previous incision

868
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:04,492
and decided to place
the xiphoid port lateral...

869
00:38:04,516 --> 00:38:07,734
<i>Halloween is not
for the faint of heart.</i>

870
00:38:07,802 --> 00:38:09,882
<i>There's a surprise
around every corner.</i>

871
00:38:10,772 --> 00:38:12,038
Rapid tests negative!

872
00:38:12,991 --> 00:38:14,140
Good for you.

873
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:15,420
I have to go back in six
months to get tested again

874
00:38:15,444 --> 00:38:17,484
to be sure, but
it's looking good.

875
00:38:17,546 --> 00:38:19,357
What's wrong? You still blind?

876
00:38:19,381 --> 00:38:20,513
Bummer.

877
00:38:20,582 --> 00:38:22,081
Mmm!

878
00:38:22,150 --> 00:38:24,117
Also, no hepatitis.

879
00:38:27,488 --> 00:38:29,066
What are you doing here?

880
00:38:29,090 --> 00:38:30,456
Dude, I'm waiting for my...

881
00:38:30,525 --> 00:38:31,691
Hi.

882
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:32,825
Jackson?

883
00:38:32,894 --> 00:38:34,193
Oh, damn it.

884
00:38:34,262 --> 00:38:37,580
I'm screwed! I'm so screwed.

885
00:38:37,649 --> 00:38:41,100
I really might never operate
again, and it's my fault.

886
00:38:41,186 --> 00:38:42,852
I went and had
surgery on my eyes

887
00:38:42,921 --> 00:38:46,389
because my glasses were
just a little bit annoying,

888
00:38:46,457 --> 00:38:48,119
and then I went
back to work too soon

889
00:38:48,143 --> 00:38:49,837
because I thought I
might get a little bit behind,

890
00:38:49,861 --> 00:38:51,944
which is so stupid.

891
00:38:52,013 --> 00:38:54,698
Yeah. Pretty stupid.

892
00:38:54,766 --> 00:38:56,548
What?

893
00:38:56,617 --> 00:38:58,296
You knew that I was gonna take
the whole day off with you, right?

894
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,697
We could have spent
the entire day at home

895
00:38:59,721 --> 00:39:01,332
on the couch while I
made you chicken soup

896
00:39:01,356 --> 00:39:03,873
and you watched
movies and slept it off.

897
00:39:03,941 --> 00:39:05,736
But, no, you had
to come to work.

898
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,071
You had to stress yourself
out and strain your eyes

899
00:39:08,095 --> 00:39:10,895
and make yourself miserable,
which I told you was gonna happen.

900
00:39:15,770 --> 00:39:16,886
Can we do it tomorrow?

901
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:18,714
We're gonna do
it right damn now.

902
00:39:19,257 --> 00:39:20,372
Come on.

903
00:39:24,813 --> 00:39:26,629
<i>Some of the surprises are good.</i>

904
00:39:26,698 --> 00:39:28,581
Hey! You made it. Hey, yeah.

905
00:39:28,650 --> 00:39:31,400
The party was great, and Sofia
is a champion apple-bobber.

906
00:39:31,469 --> 00:39:33,502
The wings look great!

907
00:39:33,571 --> 00:39:36,099
Hey, look at the little
space princess! Look!

908
00:39:36,123 --> 00:39:38,724
Hey! Go to mommy.

909
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:40,844
Hi! You want your wand?

910
00:39:40,912 --> 00:39:42,428
I don't hear any gunfire.

911
00:39:42,497 --> 00:39:44,597
Yeah, well, we'll only
get about 10 of these

912
00:39:44,666 --> 00:39:46,360
before she starts wanting
to wear slutty costumes

913
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:47,828
and run off with her
friends, and I'm not

914
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:50,770
about to cut that
number in half.

915
00:39:50,839 --> 00:39:54,256
It's the first thing Arizona and
I have agreed on in months.

916
00:39:57,929 --> 00:39:59,194
Hey.

917
00:40:20,585 --> 00:40:21,985
Who's ready to
go trick-or-treating?

918
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:25,348
Time for blast-off!
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

919
00:40:27,542 --> 00:40:29,475
All right, let's go! Whee!

920
00:40:29,944 --> 00:40:30,976
Yay!

921
00:40:31,913 --> 00:40:33,613
Um...

922
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:36,216
<i>And some of the
surprises are bad.</i>

923
00:40:36,284 --> 00:40:38,618
